{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BfTZmJuqBr6go6GQBy9Wj7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01C6TkwF18KTxXa67UkYNimN","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/improvement-plan.md","old_string":"**Fix: Protect title continuations from dedup**\n\nIn the dedup step, when the longer candidate is a multi-line join (origin `\"2-line\"` or coalesced) and the shorter is its prefix, check if the suffix word(s) are food-related (in `FOOD_DICTIONARY` or `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`). If so, prefer the longer form — it's a complete title, not an accidental substring match.","new_string":"**Fix: Protect title continuations from dedup**\n\n**Cross-iteration context:** Iteration 24 added compound-title dedup protection for titles containing explicit separators (` : ` or ` + `). That protection checks `/ [+:&] /` and is working correctly. This fix extends the same principle to multi-line joins that have no explicit separator — the continuation word is just appended. The two protections are complementary: iteration 24's handles compound titles with separators; this one handles title continuations without separators. Both coexist in the same dedup filter.\n\nIn the dedup step, when the longer candidate is a multi-line join (origin `\"2-line\"` or coalesced) and the shorter is its prefix, check if the suffix word(s) are food-related (in `FOOD_DICTIONARY` or `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`). If so, prefer the longer form — it's a complete title, not an accidental substring match."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":638,"cache_read_input_tokens":60818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":638},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe3f33e3-f5c0-4e4f-b865-ef8c5a90ce70","uuid":"6ee68a39-9a91-439b-9575-f5235da13bec"}
