p):** Not a contradiction but an integration point with iteration 24's compound-title protection. **Fixed:** Added context showing the two protections are complementary.\n\n### Overengineering Assessment\nNo overengineering detected. All 4 fixes are targeted and minimal:\n- No new abstractions or utilities beyond `applyBlindOcrRepair` (extracted from existing code)\n- No architectural changes\n- No new dependencies\n- Each fix is scoped to the specific failure pattern\n\n### Risk Areas\n- Pattern 4 (spillover threshold change) has the highest regression risk -- affects all test cases. The plan correctly sequences it last and recommends full eval after each sub-change.\n- Pattern 1 (blind OCR repair) could create false words, but is mitigated by line-position guard and hard filters.\n\n### Missing Details (Minor)\n- Open Question 2 is now resolved (not really \"open\" -- the plan says they stack with cap). Consider removing from open questions or marking as resolved."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":560,"cache_read_input_tokens":61999,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":560},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe3f33e3-f5c0-4e4f-b865-ef8c5a90ce70","uuid":"7d6d992b-b070-4df6-af7e-22c19ca3be74"}
